IS  - 2
AB  - This essay reviews briefly the nature and forms of East-West industrial cooperation, its evolution during the 1970s, and then assesses the outlook for the 1980s. In particular, the analysis seeks to determine what effects the worsening economic and political climate for cooperation may have had on its development in the latter half of the 1970s. The analysis draws on the author's own research as well as on the work of others in America and Europe.
